You will be 49 before you know it and then you can do Seafuries, the best cash i had so far, i hate RM too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nimmamen>Nimmamen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/03 3:41:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:  Re: LVL 44 And broke</span><hr size=1> 49 to do seafurys my ass... get a focused 44 fire, give him all the ac and hp stuff you can (bracers and foci and stuff) and pull to the south part of sf island.  thats by gornit spawn and the pirates.  chain cast heals as needed and let the pet damage shield take them down. im guessing 1.3%xp at 44 per kill.  Uncommon (1 in 5 ?) are gems or other vendor trash that sells 30-80pp each.  Im 1.5kpp a level here.  i was once like you but now my int is about 210 w/o kei thx to a single lvl of seafurys. @_@ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kpm2k>kpm2k</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.faceoff.com/media/pics/200211063895673-F.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 2:21:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:  Re: LVL 44 And broke</span><hr size=1> Seafurys your ass?  does that mean to do them or is there something else to kill there?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ahmish>Ahmish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 6:31:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Acryllia</span><hr size=1> Hunt Tribals in DS and sell the acryllia in the Bazaar.  I average about 2k of acryllia in about 6 hours of farming. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 9:19:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Acryllia</span><hr size=1> I think that the point is ... from about 44 on being poor is a personal choice.  You have lots of places you can farm for cash if you choose to spend the time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 5:50:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pelts</span><hr size=1> Another half-decent option might be greyhopper hides from Marus Seru; my Necro was farming them for tailoring practice at 44, and most would drop either a greyhopper hide or low quality hide, either of which should sell for a few pp in the Bazaar (or farm some spiderling silks, raise your tailoring and turn the LQ hides into leather padding at 20pp a piece). The Necro pet could kill them faster than I could find them, so a Mage pet should have no problems.<br>
<br>
Also, with care you should be able to kill shadowed men as long as you can pull them far enough away from the spawn that any clerics can't heal them... they'll be well green by 44, but heals are still a pain. Essence of Shadow is a slow seller in the Bazaar, but it's a reasonably common drop (a few pieces an hour) and when it does sell I've been making 120-150pp a piece from smiths who don't want the hassle of farming it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A> at: 2/10/03 6:06:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 6:40:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pelts</span><hr size=1> The post above is right on the money for Marus.<br>
